  "prompt": "Can educational testing services (ETS) sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visa?",
  "response": "As of the latest information available, certain nonprofit organizations, educational institutions, and government research organizations may be eligible to sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visas. Cap-exempt H-1B visas are not subject to the annual numerical limit imposed by U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS).\n\nEducational Testing Service (ETS) is a nonprofit organization specializing in educational assessments and research. Given its nonprofit status, ETS may be able to sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visas if it meets the specific criteria set forth by USCIS for cap exemption. Typically, these criteria include being an institution of higher education, a nonprofit entity related to or affiliated with an institution of higher education, a nonprofit research organization, or a government research organization.\n\nTo determine whether ETS can sponsor cap-exempt H-1B visas, it would be important to consult directly with the organization's human resources or legal department and review the most current USCIS guidelines and regulations. Additionally, consulting an immigration attorney can provide personalized and up-to-date advice tailored to individual circumstances.",
